.....<br>
<br>
These type of raids are ONLY POSSIBLE with a HIGH level tank crew, and usually a HIGH level monk puller.  The BP rule makes perfect sense to me..a 49-52 or so tank would last barely longer than i would against these uber mobs.  Paith, who is 55 plus, got his first piece of thurg armor ever the other day.  He dies about 10-15 times a raid, not counting wipeouts, to pull for us.(he makes it possible to do these raids)<br>
<br>
Dinekus just finally got the BP from thurg after many, many, many kael raids.  He also dies about 2-3 times more a raid than anyone.  Ramune also.( they make these raids possible)  without them, we wouldnt even have the chance to get this stuff.  Ummm, our highest melee in Order are all Rangers, and as bad as we like to think we are, (and we are pretty rockin) we dont make good tanks against level 56-60plus mobs.  <br>
<br>
A friend of mine is a 59 myrmidon, he has recently received a set of thurg armor.  WHY? well he single group pulls with a 60 monk, and gets the mobs that drop the armor components.  If you want this stuff, sorry to say, LEVEL! Or be patient, and it will come your way eventually, if you come to them often.<br>
<br>
I know this sounds unfair to the casual gamer, but there is plenty of  gear out there, in quests, or now with luclin many new drops.  My thurg quest arms were only a small upgrade to my Black ice sleeves, cost about 700-1k, My kromriff military leggings are comparable to thorny vine leggings(planear drop legs).  My quest helm of tracker that i will receive upon turning 55(quest all done) is comparable to any helm. My treeweave is comparable to my planear drop BP.<br>
<br>
I just feel for all the people who run these raids, die hundreds of times, and never get anything.  Then when they get a drop, theres all this dissention.  <br>
<br>
If you are a warrior, around 49-52 or so, and want the thurg armor pieces, then you can set up a kael raid.  it takes about 2-4 groups depending on average level to take these giants.  And you will still NEED a couple close to 60 tanks to take the hits, a close to 60 FD puller, and plenty of clerics to heal. (who may not be real happy about you getting the BP when others are actually tanking these mobs) <br>
<br>
And another thing, these loot policies we have been using are temporary, the raid organizers and loot coordinators are still trying to get a system that is satisfactory and maintainable.  So give it some time.  As far as people not wanting to come to raids because they cant get a BP, theres always a chance that the higher levels already have the piece, or are LD, and you may get lucky.  Luck plays an important role in these raids.  <br>
<br>
As far as the 55 rule also, maybe the alternating method may be nice...But YOU still need to have near 60 tanks getting HIT, is it fair for a tank that isnt even TANKING the mobs to have the BP over someone who is there getting the snot smacked out of em for the good of the raid?<br>
<br>
Just my opinion, and grats on all the drops guys and gals, i had fun.  I look forward to the next raid.  I personally enjoy them immensely, loot or no loot. If i get something. GREAT, if not i still had fun, and got to rumble with my buddies!<br>
<br>
rikko pheelix<br>
54 pathfinder<br>
OotBS<br>
<br>
P.S and thanks to those who make groups, and take the time to set these things up, and to all the druids who get everyone to these events, love yas<br>
